Docs:
    -- Display CSS property
    • display: inline → element will be inline:
                        - will not appear new line
                        - will not fit entire line, only the necessary width!
    • display: block → element will be block:
                     - will appear new line
                     - will fit entire line
    • display: inline-block → element will be inline-block:
                            - will appear new line
                            - will not fit entire line, only the necessary width

    • display: none              → element will disappear(is created in DOM but never render)
    • visibility: hidden         → element will be hidden for us, but the blank space will appear!
    • hidden(Html/DOM attribute) → element will be disppaear(is created in DOM but never render)
                                 → If we apply this to html element and then apply css rule to:
                                   display: block, inline,... Will appear!!   


